# SEO Metadata (All Sites)

When adding or editing HTML pages in any `site*/` folder:

- Every page must have a **unique** `<title>` of **50–60 characters** (counting rendered text, not HTML entities).
- Every page must have a **meta description** of **140–160 characters**.
- Every page must include:
  - `rel="canonical"` (absolute URL)
  - Open Graph: `og:title`, `og:description`, `og:image`, plus `og:url`, `og:site_name`, `og:type`
  - Twitter: `twitter:card`, `twitter:title`, `twitter:description`, `twitter:image`
- Metadata should be **generated from page content** (use the page’s `<h1>` + lead/intro paragraph), not copied/pasted across pages.

## Automation (preferred)

Use the repo scripts to keep this consistent:

- Update/generate metadata: `scripts/ensure-seo-meta.mjs`
- Validate constraints: `scripts/check-seo-meta.mjs`

If a new site folder is created, add a config entry in `scripts/ensure-seo-meta.mjs` (`SITE_CONFIGS`) with:
`dir`, `siteName`, `baseUrl`, and `ogImage`.

